com.contentful.java.cda

Class CDACallback<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.contentful.java.cda.CDACallback<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object to be expected as a result. Callback can be cancelled at any point using the cancel() method, that will prevent any future calls to onSuccess(T) and onFailure(RetrofitError).

    public abstract class CDACallback<T>
extends Object
    Callback to use with any of the asynchronous client methods. Implement the onSuccess(T) method for cases where the request is successful, the result object should be delivered as a parameter. It is also encouraged, but still optional to override onFailure(retrofit.RetrofitError) and provide an implementation for handling errors.

        public void cancel()
        Cancels this callback. This will prevent any future calls to onSuccess(Object) and onFailure(RetrofitError) methods. This action cannot be reversed.
